message.content:
cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.VLSI, cs.DC, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.ET (Embedded Systems) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on designing efficient embedded memory blocks for SoCs.
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is also likely as the paper proposes a holistic approach to design technology co-optimization that includes micro-architecture design.
- cs.VLSI (Very Large Scale Integration) is relevant as the paper discusses the challenges of scaling CMOS technology and proposes solutions for designing smaller and more efficient circuits.
- cs.DC (Digital Circuits) is relevant as the paper discusses the design of leaf cells, standard cells, and SRAM bitcells.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the design of a smart memory synthesis framework for embedded memory blocks.
